<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<strong><a class="nonexistent" href="./RedNaga">RedNaga</a></strong>: Gauwrach the vampire orc stopped by at the prancing pony inn, asked for lunch and... the barkeep told him they have nothing for being such as him. Oh well...<br>
 Later...<br>
 Grok the troll zombie and his friend Lohm the ent stopped at the same inn, asked for a lunch and... they served them (i don't want to know exactly what!), so they left full and satisfied.<br>
 This is racism. Either force the barkeep to serve vampires as well or (way better) stop them serving the kind of food that can fill zombies (Blargh!) <p>
<strong><a href="./NeilStevens">NeilStevens</a></strong>: Not a bug, that I know.  Serving blood is just particularly offensive to the innkeepers, while brains are actually eaten by people in some parts of the world.  In game play terms: Vampires are being given extra penalties because of their extra bonuses. 
</p>
<p>
Simon: zombies need more food to fill themselves, they should pay more gold! Or at least get a message on how rotten (or generally not considered edible by the living) the meat was and how fulfilling the zombie thought it was. (I've always been annoyed by zombies saying "Ugh! Raw meat!" or such). And there is always the question of if deathmolds are undead or now?? 
</p>
<p>
Ideally the innkeeper should remind the zombie that satisfy hunger scrolls are cheaper(when they actually are) so the innkeeper can avoid annoying other constumers with the zombie's stereotypical antics (hmmm. Some of my skin fell off. I wonder how it tastes? Sort of explains the slow digestion aspect). 
</p>
<p>
Spending the day in the inn might also be more expensive; innkeepers clearly have no love of vampires and such. 
</p>
